<br><br>
<h4>Use of Information Stored On Our Database</h4><br>
We also use information you store on our database to generate lists which may be shown to affiliates, subsidiaries, licensees, successors, and partners. That information will not be any information greater than what any person can obtain simply by publicly viewing the mechanic's and materialman's lien docket in the county where your liens will be filed and stored which shows the itemized statement that will be filed with your lien, the amount claimed, the identity of the insurance policy or policies against which the lien is asserted, if any, the name and address of the physician, hospital, ambulance, or any other type of medical provider claiming the lien, the name and address of injured person, their attorney, and the person, firm, or corporation against whom the claim is made.  Certain confidential information -- such as your password -- will not be disclosed in any of these parties. 
