<h4>Cookies</h4><br>

We are committed to providing personalized products and services to you. In order to do so, E-Lien uses cookies to store a unique identifier. A cookie is defined as a small amount of text that is sent to your browser from a Web server and stored on your computer's hard drive. If your browser is configured to enable cookies, then your browser adds the text sent to the appropriate file. Your browser will only allow E-Lien to read cookies that came from our web servers. This means that other web sites will not be able to use any information that E-Lien stores on your computer as a cookie. 
<br>
